-- Higher home prices boost D.R. Horton's profit
-- By Sagarika Jaisinghani in Bangalore
-- Thu Apr 24, 2014 07:07AM EDT
-- None



April 24 (Reuters) - D.R. Horton Inc <DHI.N>, the top U.S. homebuilder, reported an 18 percent rise in quarterly profit as it charged more for its houses, and said orders rose 9 percent.

The company's net income rose to $131.0 million, or 38 cents per share, in the second quarter ended March 31, from $111.0 million, or 32 cents per share, a year earlier. [ID:nBw7H52Rva] Homebuilding revenue rose 22.7 percent to $1.68 billion.